<TEXT>
canada is restoring diplomatic ties with iran that 
were severed when canadian embassy officials spirited six american 
diplomats out of tehran in 1980 
the canadian government said monday it decided to revive 
relations after iran dropped a demand that it apologize for 
smuggling the americans out of iran 
there were no conditions there was no apology a foreign 
ministry official told a news conference the official spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
the agreement was reached before irans announcement monday that 
it would accept a un security council resolution for a ceasefire 
in its 8yearold war with iraq 
canada closed its embassy in tehran after ambassador ken taylor 
sheltered the americans and then spirited them out of iran during 
the hostage crisis at the us embassy that began in november 1979 
since 1980 canada maintained diplomatic contact through the 
danish embassy in tehran while the iranian government was 
represented by a charge daffaires in ottawa 
under an agreement reached in tehran last week ambassadors will 
be exchanged and a canadian embassy reopened by october officials 
said 
in a formal statement both governments said restoration of full 
diplomatic relations will lead to increased exchanges in all 
fields to the mutual benefit of canada and the islamic republic of 
iran 
foreign minister joe clark said sunday that moves to improve 
diplomatic ties did not mean canada was endorsing the present 
iranian government 
but they are a significant country significant force in 
international events and it would be useful we think on the 
appropriate terms to have normal relations clark said 
he said talks on restoring relations began about a month ago as 
iran resumed normal ties with france and increased contacts with 
britain 
irans parliament speaker hashemi rafsanjani said this month 
that iran would try to cultivate better international relations 
despite the eightyear diplomatic chill canada and iran have 
remained trade partners and exchanged goods worth 228 million in 
1987 including 83 million in canadian wheat 
more than 3000 iranians received immigrant visas for canada in 
1987 
