<TEXT>
about 2000 arab americans have moved out of 
the occupied territories because the palestinian uprising has 
threatened their safety and the education of their children a us 
official said today 
us consulate spokesman david good said the 2000 arab 
americans represent about onequarter of those who lived in the 
west bank and east jerusalem before the uprising began dec 8 
on monday night some 3000 palestinians in beit sahour village 
turned a funeral into an antiisraeli demonstration after 
17yearold admon elias hilal was killed by a brick that fell from 
a fourthfloor army lookout post 
earlier in the day dutch foreign minister hans van den broek 
toured the kalandia refugee camp north of jerusalem setting off a 
protest by arab youths who chanted slogans and hurled rocks at 
reporters 
after van den broek left troops fired rubber bullets to break 
up crowds who raised outlawed palestinian flags and pictures of 
yasser arafat chairman of the palestine liberation organization 
good said the main reason the arab americans are leaving the 
occupied lands is the unsettled conditions caused by the 
palestinian rebellion many people are concerned about their 
childrens education or about them being caught up in violence 
he told the associated press 
the israeli military administration closed arabs schools in the 
west bank for four months during the uprising and cut short the 
school year by about a month the administration believes the 
schools are centers of unrest 
many of the 224 palestinians who have been killed since the 
unrest broke out are teenagers four israelis also have died 
faris bouhafa spokesman for the washingtonbased american arab 
antidiscrimination committee said some departing arab americans 
planned to return once conditions are calmer in the occupied 
territories 
bouhafa who said his 8yearold organization has 61 chapters 
and 20000 members in the united states is in israel to expand the 
role of the groups east jerusalem branch which was established 
three months ago 
