corp a private nonprofit group that finds housing for lowincome 
hispanic families in chicago 
housing or a home is the place where lives get built or 
shattered he said to the extent that a kid has a space maybe 
even their own room to study in to plan for the future is a 
very important thing 
stephen j pyne 39 an environmental historian and professional 
firefighter called his 250000 award a bolt out of the blue 
pyne who studies ways in which people have interacted with fire 
throughout history figures he was selected for doing kind of 
original stuff different kinds of things in environmental 
history 
a total of 254 macarthur fellows ranging in age from 18 to 82 
have been named since the program began in 1981 fellows receive 
their grants in increments over five years with the larger awards 
going to the older recipients winners also receive health 
insurance 
the grantmaking foundation is one of the largest private 
philanthropic groups in the united states macarthur owner of 
bankers life and casualty insurance company established it 
shortly before his death in 1978 his wife died shortly thereafter 
after he created the foundation macarthur told his board of 
directors i figured out how to make it you figure out how to 
spend it 
