spokesman who spoke on condition of anonymity he said several 
mortar rounds fell into the courtyard of the towns ancient stone 
church causing some damage the church houses six monks and 20 
nuns who were unhurt he added 
the spokesman said the clashes began sunday a day after armed 
shepherds from qoubaiyat and the jaafars engaged in a brief 
firefight over grazing rights in sheep pastures on the towns 
western edge 
two people were killed in the original clash for pastures but 
it seems the incident has developed into a shiitemaronite war 
the spokesman said he spoke on condition of anonymity 
the residents of qoubaiyat appealed to pope john paul ii in rome 
for immediate intervention to stop the military offensive against 
our peaceful town 
the appeal said there were a number of wounded people trapped 
in the town who need hospitalization 
qoubaiyat population 25000 is the fourth largest catholic 
town in north lebanon most of its younger men serve in the 
lebanese army 
the jaafar clan estimated to number about 35000 people is 
based in the central bekaa valley on the western edge of the akkar 
plateau a region traditionally dominated by maronite catholics and 
sunni moslems 
the police spokesman said the syrian command in north lebanon 
and the bekaa valley was in contact with representatives of the 
two sides to work out a lasting ceasefire 
syria the main power broker in lebanon maintains 25000 troops 
in the bekaa and north lebanon under a 1976 peacekeeping mandate 
from the 21nation arab league 
