friendofthecourt brief arguing that the use of gloves justified 
a new trial 
its like requiring a defendant to wear a prison uniform 
before a jury he said we argued that the use of gloves starts 
to stack the deck in the jurys mind toward a presumption that 
the defendant is bad or different and therefore guilty of 
something 
a lot of courts and administrators are trying to formulate a 
policy on how to deal with aids defendants and so there is a lot 
of use of the gloves in courtrooms around the country right now 
said nan hunter head of the national aclus aids and civil 
liberties project in new york 
the virus that causes acquired immune deficiency syndrome is 
