economic research service said earlier the agency said the 
increase could be in the range of 1 percent to 3 percent 
downward pressure on milk production will intensify during the 
second half of 1988 the report said concentrate grain 
prices will be much higher and forage costs will rise sharply in 
areas hit by the drought 
seasonal increases in milk prices will likely be larger than 
last year although the average price at the farm for all of 1988 
probably will be down 3 percent to 5 percent from last years 
1254 per 100 pounds the report said 
may retail prices were less than 2 percent higher than a year 
ago and only half the increase for all food or all consumer 
items the report said seasonal upswings in retail prices may 
be slightly larger than a year earlier during the second half of 
1988 however retail dairy prices probably will average only 1 
