closings from the trade bill and sent both issues back to reagan as 
separate bills 
before this summer ends we shall lead a strong initiative 
against our most serious national problem illegal drugs wright 
said sounding a theme that has shown up in national polls as the 
most ripe for political appeals the democratic congress will 
declare an allout war on drugs 
reagans response to the drug problem has been the slogan 
just say no wright observed it does little good when 
the administration is unwilling to say yes to the funding 
necessary to carry on the war 
house democratic whip tony coelho of california turned his guns 
