the fbi was hounding him 
the 31yearold defector who worked in naval intelligence while 
in the service from 197582 appeared at ease during a taped 
statement at the end of the nightly news program vremya he 
gave no details of alleged fbi persecution 
soviet media said sunday that souther asked for and was granted 
asylum 
the next day fbi spokesman thomas deaken said in washington an 
espionage investigation was launched against souther before he 
disappeared in may 1986 
for a long time i have served in the us navy souther said 
on soviet television 
he said he had recently worked in naval intelligence and had 
studied russian language and literature at old dominion university 
in norfolk va 
last year i found myself confronted with a fateful decision 
souther said i had to leave my country my family close friends 
and relatives my guilt is that i regarded my convictions and 
interests as my natural rights but the fbi thought otherwise i 
was persecuted and my freedom was threatened 
his statement delivered in english was voiced over in russian 
souther gave no details of the circumstances he faced he 
concluded his brief address by saying he turned to soviet 
authorities for asylum and fortunately for me it was granted 
souther disappeared in may 1986 after he was confronted by 
federal agents in an espionage investigation 
a vremya announcer said a special broadcast would be made 
wednesday night to better acquaint viewers with southers case 
he is the latest american to seek asylum in the soviet union 
in january theodore and cheryl branch of erie pa sought 
asylum during a tourist trip to the soviet union 
us serviceman wade roberts fled his west german base in april 
1987 and worked as a snake catcher in soviet central asia after 
being granted asylum but decided late last year to return to 
america and face desertion charges 
the arnold lockshin family of houston texas arrived in moscow 
in october 1986 complaining that they were harassed by the federal 
bureau of investigation because of their communist party 
affiliations they reportedly settled into a new life in moscow and 
have no plans to leave 
also in the soviet union is edward lee howard a former cia 
agent who defected in august 1986 howard disappeared from his 
santa fe nm home in september 1985 when the fbi was about to 
arrest him on suspicion of spying 
