the countys wild marijuana which apparently was planted years ago 
to produce hemp for rope had been discovered by entrepreneurs 
he said signs were posted to warn people of sprayed areas 
hank graddy national chairman of the sierra clubs agricultural 
committee said spraying paraquat is risky even when done manually 
if they are going to go to the trouble of walking the land it 
would seem to me that using a hatchet would be just as easy 
graddy said from his home in midway ky 
the sierra club a private environmental group maintains that 
spraying paraquat is dangerous to humans and animals in the 
vicinity but much of the debate over paraquat has focused on 
evidence that it poses serious health risks to marijuana smokers 
the dea issued a report in 1986 calling the toxic herbicides 
use to kill marijuana safe and reasonable as long as guidelines are 
followed to avoid spraying in the rain or high wind or near 
buildings and to make sure the pot is not harvested before the 
paraquat destroys it 
