<TEXT>
iran condemned tuesdays iraqi raids 
against iranian targets accused the baghdad government of 
sabotaging peace efforts and said the un chief could declare the 
start of a truce at this very moment 
but senior iraqi sources at the united nations speaking on 
condition of anonymity said they doubted that secretarygeneral 
javier perez de cuellar would succeed in his aim of achieving a 
ceasefire in a week to 10 days 
iraqs foreign minister said in baghdad on tuesday that until 
iran takes concrete action toward achieving peace iraq must keep 
on with the war 
on monday iran declared after a years delay that it 
unconditionally accepts security council resolution 598 which 
demands an immediate truce and troop withdrawal and sets out a 
peace plan to end the 8yearold iraniraq war 
irans un ambassador mohammad jaafar mahallati spelled out 
irans views after meeting perez de cuellar and after lodging a 
formal protest with the security council over iraqs air raids on a 
nuclear facility and other targets 
iraq said the air strikes were prompted by iranian attacks 
mahallati said he told the un chief that in the view of the 
authorities of iran the secretarygeneral has a totally free 
hand to declare dday at this very moment which means starting 
implementation of resolution 598 
dday is the day on which a ceasefire would begin it would be 
set by the secretarygeneral after consultations with both sides 
mahallati called the air strikes a deliberate attempt to 
sabotage the work of the secretarygeneral and the security council 
to put an immediate end to this aggressive war initiated by 
iraq 
perez de cuellar held urgent consultations with mahallati and 
later with iraqi ambassador ismat t kittani to discuss putting the 
resolution into effect and the latest iraqi attacks 
the security council held closeddoor consultations on 
resolution 598 and on irans demand to condemn the us destruction 
of an iranian airliner july 3 
the consultations ended tuesday night without any decision or 
statement and are scheduled to resume wednesday 
the secretarygenerals spokesman francois giuliani told 
reporters the un chief believes the continuation of hostilities 
is a clear sign that the ceasefire must come into place as soon as 
possible 
mahallati urged the council in a letter to condemn the iraqi 
attack which he said so defiantly mocks all efforts for 
attainment of a peaceful end to the conflict 
some diplomats said procedural matters including translating 
mahallatis letter into other official un languages would have 
to precede council discussion of this latest complaint the 
diplomats spoke on condition of anonymity 
the protest was lodged hours before the council was to discuss 
the shooting down of an iranian airliner by the us missile 
cruiser vincennes which mistook it for an attacking warplane all 
290 people on board were killed 
iran has not obtained council condemnation of the us action 
and negotiations were under way to reach a compromise statement 
which would be acceptable to all parties 
foreign minister aziz said in baghdad that iraq was on guard 
against iranian intentions and believed its decision to accept the 
ceasefire plan known as resolution 598 might be a tactical 
decision aimed at winning time or decoying with the aim of 
surprising us by initiating hostilities or preparing for more 
aggression 
aziz said that until iran takes tangible steps toward peace and 
demonstrates its sincerity it is logical to act as if the war is 
still going on 
on tuesday iraq hit iranian targets and iranian warplanes 
retaliated by raiding a dam in iraq 
iraq said a year ago that it accepts the resolution to end the 
war that began in september 1980 if iran does tehran at the time 
withheld endorsement saying iraq had to be branded the aggressor 
before there could be peace 
among other provisions resolution 598 calls for a prisoner 
exchange an impartial body to determine which side was the 
aggressor and massive international reconstruction aid 
